{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302/comments/62237679.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302/_/diff#comment-62237679"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 302, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302"}}, "title": "Refactor Playback into Playback and PlaybackHandle"}, "content": {"raw": "One method we could consider for fixing disadvantage (1) is to have the `Playback` class and all the `PlaybackHandler` instances that it spawns share a `std::shared_ptr<Log>`.\n\nSince that `Log` instance would only be held internally by classes that we control, we can ensure that the log is only being read from. Then the question becomes: Is it okay for multiple different consumers of a `Log` to be simultaneously retrieving batches using `Log::QueryMessages(~)` and then simultaneously iterating through them? I think that's a feature that we should be able to support anyhow if we can't already; otherwise our `Batch::iterator` implementation may need some work. It's probably worth writing tests for that.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>One method we could consider for fixing disadvantage (1) is to have the <code>Playback</code> class and all the <code>PlaybackHandler</code> instances that it spawns share a <code>std::shared_ptr&lt;Log&gt;</code>.</p>\n<p>Since that <code>Log</code> instance would only be held internally by classes that we control, we can ensure that the log is only being read from. Then the question becomes: Is it okay for multiple different consumers of a <code>Log</code> to be simultaneously retrieving batches using <code>Log::QueryMessages(~)</code> and then simultaneously iterating through them? I think that's a feature that we should be able to support anyhow if we can't already; otherwise our <code>Batch::iterator</code> implementation may need some work. It's probably worth writing tests for that.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-21T01:21:24.831490+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9/d42d74cf-c1bd-4431-8288-07f543bbe325/128"}}, "nickname": "mxgrey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9"}, "updated_on": "2018-04-21T01:22:12.142747+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 62237679}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302/comments/62375174.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302/_/diff#comment-62375174"}}, "parent": {"id": 62237679, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302/comments/62237679.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302/_/diff#comment-62237679"}}, "depth": 1}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 302, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302"}}, "title": "Refactor Playback into Playback and PlaybackHandle"}, "content": {"raw": "+1 to using a `shared_ptr<Log>` between `Playback` and `PlaybackHandler`.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>+1 to using a <code>shared_ptr&lt;Log&gt;</code> between <code>Playback</code> and <code>PlaybackHandler</code>.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-23T20:48:19.066277+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/692bf15758111acaddae4da15a47f9e5d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCA-0.png"}}, "nickname": "caguero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4ded1ddf-947e-4154-bbd1-3dba24f1bdbd"}, "updated_on": "2018-04-23T20:48:19.074330+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 62375174}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302/comments/62394613.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302/_/diff#comment-62394613"}}, "parent": {"id": 62375174, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302/comments/62375174.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302/_/diff#comment-62375174"}}, "depth": 2}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 302, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302"}}, "title": "Refactor Playback into Playback and PlaybackHandle"}, "content": {"raw": "Done here: 72ff62f\n\nThere's a small caveat where we can't guarantee thread safety if the user (or a different library that's running in the same application as our library) makes some configuration changes to sqlite3 during runtime, but I think the danger of that is relatively low. We're expecting all the default recommended settings of sqlite3, so if a user changes those settings, then they're taking their fate into their own hands.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Done here: <a href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/commits/72ff62f\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">72ff62f</a></p>\n<p>There's a small caveat where we can't guarantee thread safety if the user (or a different library that's running in the same application as our library) makes some configuration changes to sqlite3 during runtime, but I think the danger of that is relatively low. We're expecting all the default recommended settings of sqlite3, so if a user changes those settings, then they're taking their fate into their own hands.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-24T04:07:02.685169+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9/d42d74cf-c1bd-4431-8288-07f543bbe325/128"}}, "nickname": "mxgrey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9"}, "updated_on": "2018-04-24T04:07:02.692561+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 62394613}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302/comments/62375036.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302/_/diff#comment-62375036"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 302, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302"}}, "title": "Refactor Playback into Playback and PlaybackHandle"}, "content": {"raw": "I did minor tweaks in f660aa1, db32337.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I did minor tweaks in <a href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/commits/f660aa1\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">f660aa1</a>, <a href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/commits/db32337\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">db32337</a>.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-23T20:46:42.205362+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/692bf15758111acaddae4da15a47f9e5d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCA-0.png"}}, "nickname": "caguero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4ded1ddf-947e-4154-bbd1-3dba24f1bdbd"}, "updated_on": "2018-04-23T20:54:38.160244+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 62375036}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302/comments/62394648.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302/_/diff#comment-62394648"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 302, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/302.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/302"}}, "title": "Refactor Playback into Playback and PlaybackHandle"}, "content": {"raw": "I think I should add some tests to ensure that the new features are working as expected, but other than that I think this PR is finished.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think I should add some tests to ensure that the new features are working as expected, but other than that I think this PR is finished.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-24T04:07:40.597002+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https: